design:
## New Message Types (Webview -> Extension)

type WebMsg =
  | { type: 'board.load'; requestId: string } // Keep for backward compat - loads initial view only
  | { type: 'board.loadColumn'; requestId: string; payload: { column: BoardColumnKey; offset: number; limit: number } }
  | { type: 'board.loadMore'; requestId: string; payload: { column: BoardColumnKey } } // Auto-increments offset
  | { type: 'board.refresh'; requestId: string } // Refresh currently loaded data
  ... existing types

## Enhanced Response Types (Extension -> Webview)

type ExtMsg =
  | { 
      type: 'board.data'; 
      requestId: string; 
      payload: {
        columns: BoardColumn[];
        columnData: Record<BoardColumnKey, {
          cards: BoardCard[];
          offset: number;
          limit: number;
          totalCount: number;
          hasMore: boolean;
        }>;
        // For backward compat, also include flat 'cards' array of currently loaded
        cards: BoardCard[];
      }
    }
  | { 
      type: 'board.columnData'; 
      requestId: string; 
      payload: {
        column: BoardColumnKey;
        cards: BoardCard[];
        offset: number;
        totalCount: number;
        hasMore: boolean;
      }
    }
  ... existing types

## Handlers in extension.ts

- board.load: Load initial view (Ready + In Progress + first page of Blocked, skip Closed unless config says otherwise)
- board.loadColumn: Load specific column page
- board.loadMore: Load next page for column (track offset in extension state)
- board.refresh: Reload currently loaded ranges

## State Management in Extension

Track per-webview:
- loadedRanges: Map<BoardColumnKey, { offset: number; limit: number }[]>
- Reset on webview creation/panel disposal

notes:
UX BUG - File Watcher Refresh Spam

Issue: File watcher triggers board refresh on every DB change without debounce. Multiple rapid changes cause UI flicker and performance issues.

Fix: Add debounce to file watcher:
  let refreshTimeout: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;
  watcher.onDidChange(() => {
    if (refreshTimeout) clearTimeout(refreshTimeout);
    refreshTimeout = setTimeout(() => sendBoard(lastRequestId), 300);
  });

Estimated: 1 hour

design:
In src/extension.ts:

1. Add state tracking (per webview):
   - loadedRanges: Map<BoardColumnKey, Array<{ offset: number; limit: number }>>
   - Track what data each webview has loaded

2. Implement handlers:

async function handleLoadColumn(msg: WebMsg) {
  const { column, offset, limit } = msg.payload;

  // Call adapter.getColumnData(column, offset, limit)
  const cards = await adapter.getColumnData(column, offset, limit);
  const totalCount = await adapter.getColumnCount(column);
  const hasMore = (offset + cards.length) < totalCount;

  // Track loaded range
  loadedRanges.get(column).push({ offset, limit });

  // Send response
  post({
    type: 'board.columnData',
    requestId: msg.requestId,
    payload: { column, cards, offset, totalCount, hasMore }
  });
}

async function handleLoadMore(msg: WebMsg) {
  const { column } = msg.payload;

  // Calculate next offset from loadedRanges
  const ranges = loadedRanges.get(column) || [];
  const nextOffset = ranges.reduce((max, r) => Math.max(max, r.offset + r.limit), 0);

  // Use configured pageSize
  const pageSize = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration('beadsKanban').get<number>('pageSize', 50);

  // Delegate to handleLoadColumn logic
  ...
}

3. Modify existing board.load:
   - Load only initial columns (Ready + In Progress + first page of Blocked)
   - Use enhanced response format with columnData
   - Maintain backward compat by also including flat 'cards' array

4. Handle webview disposal:
   - Clear loadedRanges on panel.dispose()

